<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>CME&#160;407.  Soil and Site Improvement Methods.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Compaction, preloading, vertical drains, grouting, admixture stabilization, thermal stabilization, soil reinforcement, geosynthetics; construction of embankments on soft clay, embankments on mechanically stabilized earth walls, hydraulic barriers; case studies. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=CME%20315" title="CME&#160;315" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CME 315');">CME&#160;315</a>.<br />
