<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>CME&#160;430.  Theory of Elasticity I.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
The boundary value problems of linear elasticity. Uniqueness of solution. Reduction to two dimensions: the plane problems, torsion, bending. Polar coordinates and general orthogonal coordinates. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=CME%20205" title="CME&#160;205" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CME 205');">CME&#160;205</a> and <a href="/search/?P=MATH%20220" title="MATH&#160;220" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'MATH 220');">MATH&#160;220</a>; or the equivalents.<br />
