<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>CME&#160;431.  Introduction to Continuum Mechanics.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Vectors and tensors, stress, principal stresses and principal axes, deformation, compatability conditions, constitutive equations, isotropy and mechanical properties of fluids and solids. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=CME%20203" title="CME&#160;203" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CME 203');">CME&#160;203</a> and <a href="/search/?P=CME%20211" title="CME&#160;211" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CME 211');">CME&#160;211</a>; or <a href="/search/?P=CME%20203" title="CME&#160;203" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CME 203');">CME&#160;203</a> and <a href="/search/?P=ME%20211" title="ME&#160;211" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'ME 211');">ME&#160;211</a>.<br />
