<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>CME&#160;432.  Energy Methods in Mechanics.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Variational theorems of elasticity. Applications to establish approximate systems and their solution. Beams (including shear deformation.) Introduction to instability theory. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=CME%20205" title="CME&#160;205" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CME 205');">CME&#160;205</a>.<br />
