<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>CME&#160;434.  Finite Element Analysis I.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Establishment of basic finite element, matrix relations for one-dimensional heat conduction problems: Truss, beam and frame structural systems. Solution methods of the resulting equations. Introduction to two-dimensional analysis. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=CS%20109" title="CS&#160;109" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CS 109');">CS&#160;109</a>; and <a href="/search/?P=CME%20205" title="CME&#160;205" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'CME 205');">CME&#160;205</a> or <a href="/search/?P=ME%20347" title="ME&#160;347" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'ME 347');">ME&#160;347</a>.<br />
